nocodb/nocodb#5337.body:
CORS (Cross-origin resource sharing) are not activated by default. 
So, we can't use the API with a browser, in javascript

The problem exists via an `npm` installation (but one can easily add them manually):

```bash
git clone https://github.com/nocodb/nocodb-seed
cd nocodb-seed
npm install
npm install cors  # ADD THIS
```
And modify index.js before `npm start`
```js
(async () => {
    try {
        const app = require("express")();
        const { Noco } = require("nocodb");
        const cors = require("cors"); // ADD THIS
        const httpServer = app.listen(process.env.PORT || 8080);
        app.use(cors()); // ADD THIS
        app.use(await Noco.init({}, httpServer, app));
    } catch (e) {
        console.log(e);
    }
})();
```
Also with installations via the Binaries (and nothing can be done).
For Docker, not tried...

For Nococloud (yeah!!!) the problem also exists (see screenshot).

![bug-cors](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5105581/226671355-646e9902-6ea2-49b4-8daa-fb412008c540.png)

Suggestion: add the possibility to activate (or deactivate) the CORS from the admin (Teams & settings > Project Settings).

![bug-cors-api](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5105581/226671555-5a17b831-b2ca-4eff-9629-2d1d0966c5d5.png)

Or put them by default?
